&lt;h3&gt;About Ogilvy&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Ogilvy was founded in 1948 by David Ogilvy. David created a culture that deeply respects and cares about its people and clients. Our mission is to inspire people and brands to make an impact and we are committed to attracting, growing, and retaining the best talent in the industry.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we&#39;re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re on the hunt for a top notch Bilingual Public Relations Account Executive.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ogilvy is seeking a dynamic and detail-oriented Account Executive to join its PR team in Doha. This role is ideal for a communications professional looking to build strong experience in press office management, media relations, and reporting within a fast-paced agency environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of an embedded team, the Account Executive will support the delivery of strategic PR initiatives, manage day-to-day media engagement, and contribute to the successful execution of campaigns, events, and activations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role offers the opportunity to work on high-profile national initiatives while developing strong relationships across the regional media landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Press Office Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the daily operations of the account’s press office, ensuring efficient handling of media enquiries and requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and distribute press materials including press releases, media invitations, fact sheets, and briefing notes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and regularly update media databases and journalist contact lists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate internal approvals and ensure the timely dissemination of communications materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Media Relations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with local and regional media outlets, including journalists across news, lifestyle, tourism, and business sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support proactive media outreach and pitching to secure relevant coverage opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate media attendance at events, press briefings, and destination activations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in managing media visits, media tours, and journalist familiarisation programmes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Media Monitoring &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and monitor media coverage across print, online, and broadcast platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare daily monitoring updates, weekly coverage summaries, and campaign reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in producing post-event and campaign coverage reports, including insights and performance highlights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain organised archives of media coverage and reporting materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account &amp;amp; Campaign Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team in delivering integrated communications campaigns and activations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing client updates, presentations, and reporting materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate timelines and support the implementation of PR activities and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to content development and ensure high standards across all communications outputs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience in public relations, communicat

